Excellent! The keyframe has been successfully converted to grayscale (8-bit Grayscale Gray). Now I can proceed with counting objects in each frame using the object_counter skill.

```json
{
  "analysis": "The grayscale conversion was successful. Now I need to count objects (coins, enemies, turtles) in each of the 8 keyframes using the object_counter skill. I'll use the command pattern provided in the object_counter skill documentation.",
  "plan": "For each keyframe (keyframes_001.png to keyframes_008.png), I'll count coins, enemies, and turtles using the object_counter command. I'll store the results in a temporary format to later generate the CSV.",
  "commands": [
    {
      "keystrokes": "python3 /root/.claude/skills/object_counter/scripts/count_objects.py --tool count --input_image /root/keyframes_001.png --object_image /root/coin.png --threshold 0.9 --dedup_min_dist 3\n",
      "duration": 2.0
    }
  ]
}
```
